<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13759] Disable producer idempotence by default in producers instantiated by Connect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13759</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-7077&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-7077&lt;/a&gt; was merged recently referring to KIP-318. Before that in AK 3.0 idempotence was enabled by default across Kafka producers.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, some compatibility implications were missed in both cases.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If idempotence is enabled by default Connect won&apos;t be able to communicate via its producers with Kafka brokers older than version 0.11. Perhaps more importantly, for brokers older than version 2.8 the &lt;tt&gt;IDEMPOTENT_WRITE&lt;/tt&gt; ACL is required to be granted to the principal of the Connect worker.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given the above caveats, this ticket proposes to explicitly disable producer idempotence in Connect by default. This feature, as it happens today, can be enabled by setting worker and/or connector properties. However, enabling it by default should be considered in a major version upgrade and after KIP-318 is updated to mention the compatibility requirements and gets officially approved.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
